    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And this commandment have we from him,.... Either \"from God\", as the Alexandrian copy and the Vulgate Latin version read; and that to love the brethren is a commandment of God, is clear from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 3:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; or from Christ, for it is also a command of his, even his new commandment, which he has given, and his people have received from him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that he who loveth God, love his brother also; see John 13:34; which is an argument persuading to attend to the one as well as to the other; for the same command that requires the one, requires the other: and he that transgresses it in one case, is a transgressor of it, as well as in the other. ",
