      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὁ ἀγαπῶν τὸν Θεόν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " by: qui a Deo pro amante ipsius haberi vult; both false and unnecessary; for although brotherly love is the natural fruit and activity of love to God, yet at the same time the practice of it is the habitual task which he who loves God has to perform, as one appointed him by God. It is doubtful whether we are to understand by ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "αὐτοῦ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
