      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἵνα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " referring back to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ταύτην",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", it is here, as frequently after verbs of wishing and commanding, not so much the purpose as the purport of the commandment (the realization of which is certainly the aim and object of the commandment) that is stated, which Braune here also incorrectly disputes.",
